🏗️ Secure vs Vulnerable Architecture
4
⚛️ FRONTEND – React
🐞 1️⃣ XSS (Cross-Site Scripting)
❌ Vulnerable
// Profile.js
<div dangerouslySetInnerHTML={{ __html: name }} />

User-controlled URL parameter injected into DOM.

✅ Secure Version
// Profile.js
<div>{name}</div>

✔ React automatically escapes content
✔ No raw HTML rendering
✔ Eliminates DOM-based XSS

🔒 Enterprise Hardening

Add Content Security Policy (CSP)

Sanitize with DOMPurify (if HTML needed)

🐞 2️⃣ Hardcoded Secret
❌ Vulnerable
const API_SECRET = "sk_live_ABC123_SECRET";
✅ Secure Version
const API_SECRET = process.env.REACT_APP_API_SECRET;

.env (not committed):

REACT_APP_API_SECRET=xxxx

✔ No secrets in repo
✔ Use Azure App Service configuration
✔ Optionally integrate Azure Key Vault

☕ BACKEND – Spring Boot
🐞 3️⃣ SQL Injection
❌ Vulnerable
String query = "SELECT * FROM users WHERE username = '" + username + "'";
Statement stmt = connection.createStatement();
✅ Secure Version (Prepared Statement)
String query = "SELECT * FROM users WHERE username = ?";
PreparedStatement pstmt = connection.prepareStatement(query);
pstmt.setString(1, username);
ResultSet rs = pstmt.executeQuery();

✔ Prevents SQL injection
✔ Parameter binding
✔ Secure query execution

🔒 Best Practice Upgrade

Use Spring Data JPA:

public interface UserRepository extends JpaRepository<User, Long> {
    Optional<User> findByUsername(String username);
}
🐞 4️⃣ Insecure Deserialization
❌ Vulnerable
ObjectInputStream ois = new ObjectInputStream(new ByteArrayInputStream(data));
return ois.readObject();
✅ Secure Version
@PostMapping("/safe")
public User createUser(@RequestBody User user) {
    return userService.save(user);
}

✔ Uses JSON mapping
✔ No arbitrary object execution
✔ Eliminates RCE risk

🐞 5️⃣ Hardcoded Database Password
❌ Vulnerable
spring.datasource.password=admin123
✅ Secure Version
spring.datasource.password=${DB_PASSWORD}

Set in Azure App Service:

DB_PASSWORD=secure-prod-value

✔ No secret in code
✔ Secure config injection
✔ Production-ready

🐞 6️⃣ Broken Authentication
❌ Vulnerable
if (role.equals("admin")) {
    return "Welcome Admin";
}

User controls role parameter.

✅ Secure Version (Spring Security)
@PreAuthorize("hasRole('ADMIN')")
@GetMapping("/admin")
public String adminPanel() {
    return "Welcome Admin";
}

✔ Role-based access control
✔ Enforced server-side
✔ Cannot bypass via query param

